<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-10-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-10-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="534" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d534">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/694.]</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-10-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">October 21, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The President announced by proclamation this afternoon his retirement
                            from office July 1, 1914, and elections are set for May, 1914. Amnesty
                            guaranties and release of political prisoners decreed; also return of
                            citizens from abroad; foreigners not mentioned. The entire Cabinet will
                            resign, the President will return all resignations, after which the
                            Minister of War, for patriotic reasons, will decline to serve any
                            longer. The Minister’s brother will also resign.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>